  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Chronic\nmyeloproliferative disorder\nAbnormal proliferation is seen in all 3 cell lines\nTypically in elderly\nCan be asymptomatic or symptomatic\nCommonly caused by JAK2 mutation",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "myeloproliferative disorder",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Myeloproliferative_disorders"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Severe burning pain in the hands or feet accompanied by a reddish or bluish coloration of the skin\nSuspected with any combination of the following:\n[1]\nAbnormally\nelevated\nhemoglobin levels (>18 g/dL in men; 16 g/dL in women)\nNormal oxygen saturation\nBleeding complications\nPortal vein thrombosis\nSplenomegaly\nPlethora\nPruritus\nafter bathing\nMay develop\nhyperviscosity syndrome",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Pruritus",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Pruritus"
        },
        {
          "text": "hyperviscosity syndrome",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Hyperviscosity_syndrome"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Differential_Diagnosis": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Polycythemia_(Erythrocytosis)": {
          "text": "Primary polycythemia (\nmyeloproliferative disorders\n)\nPolycythemia vera\nEssential thrombocytosis\nChronic myelogenous leukemia\n(CML)\nLeukemoid Reaction\nMyelofibrosis\nSecondary polycythemia (due to increased EPO)\nChronic\nhypoxemia\n(e.g.\nCOPD\n, physiologic\naltitude\nadaptations or\nchronic mountain sickness\n)\nCarboxyhemoglobin (chronic smokers)\nRenal cyst or hydronephrosis\nEPO-secreting tumors (RCC,\nhepatocellular carcinoma\n)\nAnabolic steroid abuse\nAbnormal hemoglobins",
          "tables": []
        }
